rtue of self-control; and on what men feared.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aMasculinityxHistoryxClassical agexGreecexAthens. 0aMasculinityzGreecezAthensxHistoryyClassical age. 0aMasculinityzGreecezAthensxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aRhetoric, Ancient. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh  aancient athens.  aancient greece.  aancient world.  aathenian masculinity.  aathens.  aattic.  ademos.  adomesticity.  aeconomic status.  aeros.  afathers and sons.  afear.  agender studies.  agender.  agreed.  agreek men.  ahead of household.  ahellenism.  ahomosexuality.  ahonor.  ahusband.  akharis.  akinship.  akurios.  amanhood.  amanliness.  amanly values.  amanly virtue.  amarriage.  amasculine shame.  amasculinity.  amens studies.  amilitary.  anonfiction.  apeace.  apity.  apleasure.  apolitics.  apride.  arhetoric.  aself control.  asexuality.  ashame.  asocial history.  ason.  astatus.  aviolence.  awar.  awealth.  ayouth.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093113840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520931138423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520931138/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles